TITLE: Texas drive-by shooting at family BBQ leaves 2 dead, 5 wounded: police
SUMMARY: Two men were killed and five other victims were wounded after a suspect drove by a family barbeque in San Antonio and unloaded multiple rounds, authorities said.

TITLE: Hundreds gather for vigil remembering two California police officers killed in shootout
SUMMARY: A vigil was held in El Monte, California, honoring fallen officers Michael Paredes and Joseph Santana, who died following a shootout in the Los Angeles County city.

TITLE: Number of Americans who believe in God drops to historic low: Poll
SUMMARY: The number of Americans who believe in God is at the lowest in nearly seven decades, as Gallup notes religiosity is a major factor in US political divisions.

TITLE: Third suspect charged in Chicago mass shooting at McDonald’s near Magnificent Mile
SUMMARY: Chicago police say a 17-year-old turned himself in on a gun offense, making him the third suspect arrested following a mass shooting at a McDonald’s near Magnificent Mile last month.

TITLE: Wisconsin mom says school district threatening legal action to 'bully' her criticism to silence
SUMMARY: A Wisconsin mom said that the Oconomowoc School District is trying to bully her into silence by threatening legal action for her critical statements.

TITLE: Texas gun owner shoots teen during alleged attempted robbery
SUMMARY: A gun owner in Texas defended himself and a female companion after a group of young men with long criminal histories attempted to rob the couple at gunpoint, police say.

TITLE: Pro-choice protesters descend on Coney Barrett's home with blood and doll props
SUMMARY: Members of Rise Up 4 Abortion Rights protested outside of Supreme Court Justice Amy Coney Barrett's home in Virginia demanding "abortion on demand and without apology."

TITLE: Number of Americans who think the US has poor moral values hits record high: Poll
SUMMARY: A Gallup poll found that half of Americans rate the US as having poor moral values, while only one percent said that the country's moral values are excellent.

TITLE: Texas woman pleads guilty on 26 counts of voter fraud over alleged vote harvesting operation
SUMMARY: A Texas woman pleaded guilty to voter fraud, including counts for illegal voting, unlawful possession of a mail ballot, and running a vote-harvesting operation.

TITLE: LAPD form skirmish line after officers pummeled with fireworks, bottles during 'street takeover'
SUMMARY: Los Angeles "street takeover" drivers allegedly hurled fireworks, rocks and bottles at officers attempting to disperse crowds, forcing police to establish a skirmish line.

TITLE: Yellowstone National Park to partly reopen after floods
SUMMARY: Yellowstone National Park officials announced Saturday the park will partially reopen to visitors via a temporary license plate system after major flooding in the park.

TITLE: Massachusetts bishop revokes Catholic affiliation from school for flying pride, BLM flags
SUMMARY: Massachusetts Bishop Robert J. McManus penned a decree stripping The Nativity School of Worcester of its Catholic affiliation for flying Black Lives Matter and pride flags.

TITLE: Florida mom helps save two girls from alleged kidnapper after getting bad feeling: Report
SUMMARY: David Daniels, 37, was arrested last week in Fishhawk, Florida, after an alert mother felt something was wrong upon spotting him following two young girls by a local church.

TITLE: Mayor Eric Adams ready to back naming street honoring Otto Warmbier
SUMMARY: The street outside North Korea's U.N. mission in Manhattan is the proposed site for 'Otto Warmbier Way,' and would commemorate the life of the young American.

TITLE: Louisville mayor punched in random retail store attack
SUMMARY: Law enforcement are looking for an unidentified man who punched Louisville Mayor Greg Fischer in a random attack at a retail outlet on Saturday, police announced.

TITLE: Virginia alleged thieves siphon thousands of dollars of fuel from gas station, advertise discounts online
SUMMARY: Two suspects were arrested for allegedly stealing thousands of dollars worth of fuel from a Virginia Beach gas station and reselling it online at discounted rates, police say.

TITLE: Ted Bundy was intrigued by Green River killer Gary Ridgway for this reason, doc says: 'Worries were reality'
SUMMARY: Gary Ridgway, a serial killer, terrorized the Seattle area in the 1980's. Since 2003, he has pleaded guilty to killing 49 women and girls.Investigator Dave Reichert tirelessly led the case.

TITLE: 9-foot Florida alligator eats 40-pound dog, owner says: 'Took him down like it was nothing'
SUMMARY: A man and his dog were unexpectedly attacked by an alligator while the two were playing fetch at a local park. Wildlife officials said later the alligator was 9-feet, 2-inches in length.

TITLE: Small plane crash leaves 2 dead in Arizona
SUMMARY: Authorities have identified the two victims of a plane crash, who died after their small plane when down in the Arizona desert.

TITLE: Virginia inmates escape from federal prison
SUMMARY: Four inmates from a federal prison in Hopewell, Virginia are missing, the U.S. Bureau of Prisons said Saturday. An internal investigation into how the prisoners escaped is underway.
